args: My future self clearly said that if I go on a\nsummer seaside vacation, my experiment\nwill be a success.
But what am I meant to DO here?\nHow do vacations even work?\nNo textbook prepared me for this!
Is something troubling you, Sinoa?\nAren't you going to go have some fun?
I feel extremely silly confessing this, but...\nI'm at a loss over what to actually do here.
How about you start with a little swim?
I-I suppose I could try, but, well...\nI've been a bookworm since I was a child.\nPhysical exercise isn't really my forte.
The one time I ventured to a nearby river,\nI wasn't even able to float, let alone\nactually swim.
Ever since, I've been reluctant to tempt\nfate again. The experience haunts me,\nto be completely honest.
I see. In that case, I shall teach you how.
What? N-no, you don't have to—
Breathe, Sinoa. Anyone can swim\nonce they grasp the fundamentals.\nThe human body is buoyant by nature.
You're telling me that human flotation is\nnot merely possible, but a law of nature?
In other words, my previous failure\nstemmed purely from my ignorance\nof hydrodynamic theory?!
Er...yes? I suppose you could say that?
Fascinating! Then the problem is\nalready solved! Theoretically.
Thank you, Elisanne. Now that I understand\nthe root of my previous failure, I am ready\nto yield to the sea's embrace!
Well, I'm glad you feel more comfortable\nwith the concept of swimming.
Shall we head down to the water and give\nit a try? After stretching, of course.
Of course! You have my gratitude in\nadvance for your expert tutelage!
Are you all right?!\nHere, hold on to me!

I'm not sure even a boulder could
have beaten you to the bottom.
You said you couldn't float,
but I had no idea it was this bad.
Indeed. But why? Operating under the\nfundamental assumption that humans\nfloat—
WAIT! Is this—no, surely not! Is this\nconclusive proof that I'm NOT HUMAN?!
Let's get you some floaties to practice\nwith. Wait here. I'll go fetch them.
That seems prudent. Surely, if I make use\nof a flotation device's buoyancy, I can...\nHm. Hmmm. Hmmmmm...
Eureka! Humans and floaties...\nare ONE AND THE SAME!
Perhaps we should get you out of the sun...
Hear me out. Both humans and floaties are\ninnately buoyant, yes? They rise in water.
And WHY do they rise in water? AIR!\nSo if I take in a big breath—
I did it! I'm floating! I'm floating, Elisanne!

Superb! Breath control IS a crucial part
of learning to float. I'm impressed that
you figured that out through deduction
rather than practice.
Heh heh. Reasoning about natural\nphenomena is a researcher's bailiwick!
So, how do I move my body once\nI'm afloat?
Right! Let's start with the scissor kick. Lay\nyour body flat, then take your legs and...
Indeed. It's a wonderful full-body workout.\nNow, are you still with me, Sinoa?
Y-yes! I'm fine! Bone-tired, but...\nstrangely exhilarated!

The feeling of propelling myself through
water with my own deliberate movements
is something I'd have never experienced
had I stayed huddled in the lab.
I would say that CERTAINLY counts as\nenjoying my seaside vacation, so surely\nmy next experiment will—
Hrk! I can't move another inch...
Easy, now. You need to rest.\nI'll carry you back to our lodgings.
The moment Sinoa's head hit the pillow,\nshe slept like the dead until the following day.
Ahhh, what a beautiful morning! I'm\nfeeling wide awake and sharp as a tack.
Perhaps because I slept so well?

No, it's because I gave my body the
exercise it sorely needed. And now that
I'm in peak condition, my experiment is
practically guaranteed to bear fruit.
Thank you, future self!\nYour guidance was foolproof!
Now, let the sciencing begin!\nSpace-time distortion field... Activate!
Internal mana density has reached the\ncontrol value. Pressure valve readout is\ngreen.
Everything looks good. Now, once the\nmana density stabilizes, I can...
What? Th-the density is spiking!\nIt's going to—
No. I won't accept this.\nIt was going perfectly this time!\nRight up to the very last step...

A-HA! Clearly, this means I haven't
sufficiently enjoyed my seaside vacation
yet. I need to put my nose to the
grindstone and relax harder than ever.
I'll need to solicit more help so I can\nreally crank the fun dial up to eleven!
